Before (1.x)After (2.0) <pre><code>CWSButton("Delete account", isDanger: true) { delete() }
</code></pre> <pre><code>CWSButton("Delete account", variant: .danger) { delete() }
</code></pre> <p>How consumers migrate safely:</p> <ol> <li>Upgrade to the last <code>1.x</code> — deprecation warnings light up every affected call site.</li> <li>Apply Xcode's Replace with fix-it (powered by <code>renamed:</code>) across the project.</li> <li>Build clean (no warnings) → bump to <code>2.0.0</code>.</li> </ol> <p>The overlap is the point: a consumer is never forced to rewrite and upgrade in the same step.</p>
